## Data Flow

### Static site data
`utils/constant.js` exports `NavItems`, `PROJECTS`, and `WORK` вЂ” plain JS arrays imported directly into page files.

### Blog posts (MDX)
- Each post lives at `pages/blogs/<slug>/index.mdx`.
- Wraps its content in `<BlogPost meta={...}>` from `components/BlogPost.js`.
- `getAllPosts.js` uses `require.context` to glob all `.mdx` files under `pages/blogs/` at build time and returns `{ slug, meta }` pairs for the `/blogs` listing page.

### External data (build-time)
Both fetches happen in `getStaticProps`, so the API calls run at **build time** only (static HTML generated):
- **YouTube** вЂ” `https://www.googleapis.com/youtube/v3/search` with `process.env.API_KEY`.
- **Medium** вЂ” `https://api.rss2json.com/v1/api.json?rss_url=https://medium.com/feed/@saumyanayak`.

> вљ пёЏ `API_KEY` is exposed to the client bundle via `next.config.js` `env:{}`. Consider moving YouTube fetch to a server-only API route or using `NEXT_PUBLIC_` naming intentionally.

