## Styling

- **Tailwind utilities** throughout; no CSS Modules.
- **Dark mode** is toggled manually by adding/removing the `dark` class on `<html>` (`helpers.js` + `Switch.jsx`). Tailwind's `darkMode: 'selector'` picks this up.
- **CSS variables** `--bg-color-primary` set in `globals.css` for body background in each theme.
- **Global rule:** `text-transform: lowercase` applied to `body` in `globals.css`.

---

## Components

### `Layout.js`
Shell around every page. Renders the header text "hello", desktop nav tabs (from `NavItems`), a hamburger/mobile nav, and the `<Switch>` theme toggle. Active nav item is derived from `useRouter().pathname`.

### `BlogPost.js`
Wrapper used by every `.mdx` post. Injects a `<Head>` with Open Graph / canonical SEO tags built from the `meta` prop, renders the post title and date, then `{children}` (the MDX body).

### `Switch.jsx`
Single-purpose toggle button that calls `helpers.js` to flip the `dark` class and persist preference.

---

## SEO

- `next/head` in each page file provides per-page `<title>`, `<meta description>`, Open Graph tags, and `<link rel="canonical">`.
- Canonical base URL in page components: `https://saumyanayak.xyz`.
- `next-sitemap` generates `sitemap.xml` and `robots.txt` into `public/` at build time; configured with `siteUrl: 'https://www.saumyaone.xyz'`.

> вљ пёЏ Domain inconsistency: pages reference `saumyanayak.xyz`, `home-on-internet.vercel.app`, and `saumyaone.xyz` across different files. Consolidate to one canonical domain.

---

## Known Issues

- `pages/reachme.js` has a malformed JSX fragment (`"re"` after `className`).
- `pages/learnings.js` default export is named `Projects` (copy-paste artifact).
- Multiple `WORK` entries share `id: 4`, causing duplicate React keys.
- YouTube `API_KEY` is client-bundle-exposed via `next.config.js` `env:{}`.
